member.summary:
The data pattern attribute applies a data source to a fixture or test parameter declaratively. It can be attached to a fixture class, a public property or field of a fixture, a test method or a test method parameter. When attached to a property or field of a fixture, implies that the property or field is a fixture parameter (so the may be omitted).
The order in which items contributed by a data pattern attribute are use can be controlled via the property. The contents of data sets with lower order indices are processed before those with higher indices.
// Ensures that the rows are processed in exactly the order they appear. [Test] [Row(1, "a"), Order=1)] [Row(2, "b"), Order=2)] [Row(3, "c"), Order=3)] public void Test(int x, string y) { ... }
This class is and so cannot be instantiated.
